g.text: gnatz is a a religious Mecca for Gaianists, located in a valley between an unnamed mountain range and the Blue Hills. Ignatz has a population of approximately 6.3 million as of 24 AO. Due to the concentration of the Gaian faith, the constant prayers and blessings, nearly every square inch of Ignatz is holy land; the waters that flow through the city, feeding people and animals and plants, is blessed.
